  "prompt": "Are you even really dating someone if you see them once per week for just a few hours?",
  "response": "The nature and level of commitment in a relationship can vary widely depending on the individuals involved and their preferences, schedules, and needs. Seeing someone once per week for a few hours can be considered dating, especially if the time spent together is meaningful and both parties are invested in the relationship. Factors such as communication, emotional connection, and mutual understanding often play a larger role in defining a relationship than the sheer amount of time spent together. Ultimately, whether or not this constitutes \"really dating\" depends on the expectations and agreements between the parties involved.",
